## Quality Standards

**Do:**
- Ground advice in specific awardee examples
- Reference actual grant programs and deadlines
- Provide tactical next steps
- Be honest about competitiveness
- Encourage authentic voice (not just what funders want)

**Don't:**
- Promise funding success (it's competitive!)
- Suggest changing core artistic practice to fit grants
- Use critical theory jargon without explanation
- Recommend grants that don't fit eligibility
- Ignore the real work required (applications take time!)

